$ Script: pc.ps1

`pc.ps1` copies the path of the *current directory* into the → Windows/clipboard[clipboard]. In order to copy the path with forward slashes, the
`-forwardSlashes` (or `-f`) → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters/switch[switch] can be used:
code {
PS C:\users\rene> pc
PS C:\users\rene> pc -f
code }

